      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can imagine the frustration of being stuck at Heathrow, especially when you're trying to get to Singapore. To find a new flight, you'll want to prioritize the most important factors, which are often the same as those that determine a successful trip: speed, reliability, and flexibility. You'll want to look for flights with the shortest layovers, the fewest connections, and the most direct routes. It's a good idea to compare prices and schedules across multiple airlines to find the best option for your needs. \n\nYou might also consider using flight comparison websites, which can help you find the most efficient and affordable flights. Some websites even offer features that allow you to track your flight status and receive notifications when your flight is rebooked or when there are any changes to your travel plans. \n\nAs you navigate the chaos of Heathrow, take a deep breath and remember that you're not alone. Many travelers have been in your shoes before, and with a little patience and persistence, you'll find a new flight that gets you to Singapore quickly and efficiently.",
