    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can almost hear the chaos of Heathrow from here. It's a bit like a big, messy puzzle, with all the pieces not quite fitting together. As for what to do, I'd say it's a bit like a game of \"Goblin's Gambit\" - you have to weigh the risks and benefits of each option.\n\nWaiting for the airline to rebook you might be a safer bet, but it could also mean waiting for a long time, and who knows when they'll get it right? On the other hand, trying to find your own flight through a different airline might be a bit more unpredictable, but it could also give you more control over your travel plans.\n\nOne thing to consider is that airlines often have a \"Goblin's Clause\" in their contracts - you know, that fine print that says they can change your flight plans at the last minute without notice. So, if you do decide to go the DIY route, make sure you read the fine print and understand the risks.\n\nThat being said, if you're feeling adventurous and want to take matters into your own hands, you could try using a flight comparison website to see what options are available. Just be aware that the airline's policies and restrictions might change",
